<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-05-20T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-05-20T17:00:00-05:00" n="148" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d148">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">837.51 Cooperation Program/79a:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Messersmith</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-05-20T18:00:00-04:00">May 20, 1941—6
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>127. The Export-Import Bank requests that you make it clear to the Cuban
                            authorities that the old $4,000,000 credit<note n="79" xml:id="d148fn79">This refers to the conditional offer of $4,000,000 credit contained
                                in note to the Cuban Ambassador, December 4, 1940, <ref target="frus1940v05#pg_784"><hi rend="italic">Foreign
                                        Relations</hi>, 1940, vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">v</hi>, p.
                                    784</ref>.</note> has been superseded by the new $25,000,000
                            arrangement, and has been canceled.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>